  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Add your <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a small heatproof bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Heat a pot with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat for 1-2 min or until very hot then carefully pour the heated oil into the bowl, give it a good mix up and set aside for later, reserving the pot – this is your <strong>chilli oil</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweetcorn-based-pizza-with-chorizo-chilli-oil-and-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Put a large baking tray (or two) in the oven to heat up (this will stop your <strong>pizza bottoms</strong> from going soggy!)</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Drain your <strong>sweetcorn</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweetcorn-based-pizza-with-chorizo-chilli-oil-and-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reheat the reserved pot with a knob of <strong>butter </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>drained sweetcorn </strong>and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 3-4 min further or until the sweetcorn is tender</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweetcorn-based-pizza-with-chorizo-chilli-oil-and-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain your <strong>mozzarella</strong>, then pat and squeeze as much liquid out as you can with kitchen paper</p><p>Tear the <strong>drained mozzarella</strong> into rough, bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweetcorn-based-pizza-with-chorizo-chilli-oil-and-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once tender, add the <strong>sweetcorn</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> with a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>sweetcorn purée</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweetcorn-based-pizza-with-chorizo-chilli-oil-and-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the heated tray[s] from the oven and add the <strong>pizza base[s]</strong></p><p>Divide the <strong>sweetcorn purée</strong> between the <strong>pizza base[s] </strong>and spread it evenly all over them with the back of a spoon</p><p>Top with your<strong> diced chorizo</strong> and <strong>torn mozzarella</strong> and return the tray[s] to the oven for 12-15 min or until the cheese has melted and the bases are crisp – this is your <strong>chorizo & sweetcorn pizza</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweetcorn-based-pizza-with-chorizo-chilli-oil-and-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pizza is cooking, strip your <strong>coriander</strong> from their stalks, discard the stalks</p><p>Trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong> then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/sweetcorn-based-pizza-with-chorizo-chilli-oil-and-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>chorizo & sweetcorn pizza</strong> with the <strong>salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish the pizza with the <strong>coriander</strong>, <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>and <strong>chilli oil </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Drizzle the salad with your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>and a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
